**Implementation of DFS for a graph:**

- It traverses each node in the graph and checks whether any of the nodes in the graph are visited.
- When a node is visited, it adds its path to the queue.
- At every iteration, it prints the path and then removes the nodes from the queue.

```java
class DFS {
  public void dfs(Graph g) {
    int[] visited = new int[g.size()];
    Queue<Vertex> q = new LinkedList<>();
    for (Vertex v : g.vertexSet()) {
      visited[v] = 1;
      q.add(v);
    }
    while (!q.isEmpty()) {
      Vertex v = q.poll();
      System.out.println(v);
      for (int i = 0; i < visited[v]; i++) {
        if (i != 0) {
          System.out.println("->");
        }
        System.out.println(v);
      }
    }
  }
}
```

