### 11.7.5. BFS

**Implementation of BFS for a graph:**

- It traverses each node in the graph in a pre-order traversal.
- When a node is visited, it prints the path and then removes the nodes from the queue.

```java
class BFS {
  public void bfs(Graph g) {
    Queue<Vertex> q = new LinkedList<>();
    for (Vertex v : g.vertexSet()) {
      q.add(v);
    }
    while (!q.isEmpty()) {
      Vertex v = q.poll();
      for (Vertex u : g.adjacentVertexSet(v)) {
        System.out.println(v + "->" + u);
        if (v != u) {
          q.add(u);
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

